"subsection_index": 3, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.5, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.5 The public is entitled to obtain copies of some of the documents that parties file at court unless the court has ordered otherwise. Please see further sections within this guide on online public search, open justice, anonymity, confidential documents, non disclosure orders and Tomlin orders and see CPR5.4B and 5.4C and PD5A.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_4", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.5", "subsection_index": 4, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.6, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.6 It is the duty of all parties to litigation, whether represented or not, to bring relevant matters to the attention of the court and not to mislead the court. This means for example that they must not misrepresent the law and must therefore inform the court of any relevant legislation or previous court decisions which are applicable to their case and of which they are aware (whether favourable or not to their case); and must draw the court's attention to any relevant irregularity.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_5", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.6", "subsection_index": 5, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.7, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.7 In addition, there is a particular duty when an application is made to the court without the other party being present (for example in the case of urgency or when seeing a judge at an 'Application without Notice'). Here the litigant is under a duty to disclose any facts or other matters (including arguments of fact or of law) which might be relevant to the court's decision, even if adverse to their case, and specifically draw the court's attention to such matters.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.7", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.8, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.8 In many cases the parties will need legal assistance, whether by way of advice, drafting, representation at hearings or otherwise. It is not the function of court staff to give legal advice; however, subject to that, they will do their best to assist any litigant. Judges are not in a position to give advice about the conduct of a claim", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_7", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.8", "subsection_index": 7, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.9, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.9 There is general information available to litigants in person on the judiciary website here: Advice for Litigants in Person - Courts and Tribunals Judiciary", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_8", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.9", "subsection_index": 8, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.10, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.10 The following is a non-exhaustive list of sources of assistance to litigants in person.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_9", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.10", "subsection_index": 9, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.11, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.11 Litigants in person who are enquiring as to the possibility of obtaining legal assistance or representation through legal aid may contact Civil Legal Advice at 03453454345 ( 9.00 am to 8.00 pm Monday to Friday and 9.00am to 12.30 pm on Saturdays) or on the website at https://www.gov.uk/civil-legal-advice. In general, while the availability of legal aid has become very restricted under the Legal Aid, Sentencing and Punishment of Offenders Act 2012, applicants will probably be directed to pursue their enquiries via firms of solicitors practising in areas of legal aid.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_10", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.11", "subsection_index": 10, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.12, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.12 An online service which provides practical information on rights and the law in England and Wales. https://www.advicenow.org.uk/", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_11", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.12", "subsection_index": 11, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.13, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.13 There is an RCJ Advice Bureau off the Main Hall at the RCJ. The Bureau runs an appointment-based service. To request an appointment, applicants should complete the civil triage form available on their website (www. rcjadvice.org.uk) and email it to them at civiltriage@rcjadvice.org or call into the office to complete the form between 9.30am and 1pm and 2pm and 4.30pm weekdays. Their website has details on all their services and how to access them (www.rcjadvice.org.uk)", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_12", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.13", "subsection_index": 12, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.14, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.14 Support Through Court (previously known as The Personal Support Unit (PSU)) is an independent charity which supports litigants in person, witnesses, victims, their family members and other supporters attending the Royal Courts of Justice and other courts across the country. Requests vary from the very simple to the complex. Some people just require directions or advice about procedures. Others need to unburden themselves, while others request the moral and emotional support of being accompanied in court. STC can be particularly helpful for clients with special needs.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_13", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.14", "subsection_index": 13, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.15, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.15 The volunteers are not lawyers and cannot provide legal advice or representation. They can provide procedural information, help to organise and complete paperwork, look up relevant information and discuss settling issues without going to court. They can help before hearings by helping litigants put their thoughts in order, provide emotional support in court and make sure the litigant understands what was discussed in the hearing and the next steps.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_14", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.15", "subsection_index": 14, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.16, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.16 The office in the RCJ is open Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Fridays from 10.30am to 4 pm (closed for lunch between 1 and 1.45 pm ). Walk-ins are accepted subject to availability. Face-to-face and remote appointments can be booked in advance: https://www.supportthroughcourt.org/locations/ london/rcj-appointment/.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_15", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.16", "subsection_index": 15, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.17, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.17 Support for general enquiries is available on 02045205959 on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Fridays from 10.30am to 12.30pm.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_16", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.17", "subsection_index": 16, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.18, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.18 Its address is: Thomas Moore Building (ground floor), Royal Courts of Justice, Strand WC2A 2LL. Tel: 02045205959.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_17", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.18", "subsection_index": 17, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.19, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.19 There are charities through which qualified Lawyers provide advice without charge (known as "pro bono") for some cases. See https://www.lawworks. org.uk/ and https://weareadvocate.org.uk/.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_18", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.19", "subsection_index": 18, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.20, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.20 Advocate is the national pro bono charity of the Bar. They find barristers for people in England and Wales who are not eligible for legal aid and cannot afford to pay for legal assistance. They help with: Specialist legal advice, drafting and representation and help at mediation. Advocate works exclusively with barristers and, as such, can only consider cases that are appropriate for barrister assistance. In essence this means that it would need to be representation in a court or Tribunal in England or Wales or advice or drafting suitable for a barrister to provide. In practice this means different things for different areas of law. Applicants should visit www.weareadvocate. org.uk for information about how to apply.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_19", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.20", "subsection_index": 19, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.21, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.21 Barristers who are qualified to work under the direct access scheme can be contacted directly by litigants. This is not a free legal advice scheme but enables litigants to instruct a barrister directly to assist them for example with a court hearing. Further details can be found through the Bar Council direct access portal: Homepage (directaccessportal.co.uk)", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_20", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.21", "subsection_index": 20, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.22, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.22 Hearings are dealt with more fully in Section 9 below, to which reference should be made. See in particular 9.88-9.89 about contacting the court in advance of any hearings if assistance is required to access the court due to disability or other vulnerability of a party or witness.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_21", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.22", "subsection_index": 21, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.23, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.23 Ordinarily, the claimant or applicant is asked to put together an indexed and paginated file of the relevant documents for the court for the purposes of the hearing (called hearing bundles). Where a claimant or applicant is unrepresented, a represented defendant or respondent may be directed to provide the hearing bundles. Parties often file at court, and serve on the other parties, skeleton arguments (written summaries of their arguments and submissions) before a hearing.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_22", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.23", "subsection_index": 22, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.24, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.24 Litigants in person should identify in advance of any hearing those points which they consider to be their strongest points, and they should put those points first in their oral and any written submissions to the court.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_23", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.24", "subsection_index": 23, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.25, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.25 Before a hearing starts a litigant in person should be given by any other party, and should provide to other parties, photocopies of any legal authorities (past judicial decisions and/or statutes and/or textbooks) which are to be cited to the court in addition to any skeleton argument(s). These should be provided well before the hearing rather than at the door of the court.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_24", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.25", "subsection_index": 24, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.26, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.26 In drafting proposed or actual case management directions the parties and the court should make use of any relevant standard directions (which can be found online at http://www.justice.gov.uk//courts/procedure-rules/civil) and adapt them to the circumstances of the case.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_25", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.26", "subsection_index": 25, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.27, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.27 Any legal representative in the case should ask the litigant in person to give their name (and to give details of any special arrangements that they may wish to request e.g. in consequence of any disability) to the usher or in-court support staff if they have not already done so.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_26", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.27", "subsection_index": 26, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.28, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.28 Proper allowances in relation to hearings will be made in recognition of the difficulties facing litigants in person. The court will aim to enable the unrepresented party's case to be put forward in a way which ensures that the proceedings are conducted fairly.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_27", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.28", "subsection_index": 27, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.29, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.29 Where a litigant in person is the applicant, the court may ask one of the represented parties to speak first in court and explain the case briefly and impartially, and to summarise the issues.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_28", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.29", "subsection_index": 28, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.30, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.30 The Judge may ask a litigant in person the matters about which their witness may be able to give evidence or on which a witness called by another party ought to be cross-examined, and if necessary put to the witness such questions as the court considers proper.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_29", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.30", "subsection_index": 29, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.31, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.31 If a litigant in person wishes to give oral evidence he or she will generally be required to do so from the witness box in the same manner as any other witness of fact.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_30", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.31", "subsection_index": 30, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.32, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.32 At the end of the hearing, the judge will explain the Order they make. Representatives for other parties should also explain the court's order after the hearing if the litigant in person does not appear to understand it.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_31", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.32", "subsection_index": 31, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.33, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.33 A litigant in person may be assisted at any hearing by an unqualified person (often referred to as a McKenzie friend) subject to the discretion of the court. The Court will generally consider a request by the litigant in person to have a McKenzie friend in accordance with the Guidance in Practice Note (McKenzie friends: Civil and Family Courts) [2010] 1 WLR 1881.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_32", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.33", "subsection_index": 32, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.34, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.34 There is a presumption that a McKenzie friend should be permitted but the Guidance gives various examples of reasons as to why they might not. Different considerations may apply where the person seeking the right of audience is being paid or remunerated to do so and litigants in person applying to have a McKenzie friend should be prepared to disclose whether the McKenzie friend is being paid or remunerated and if so how the pay or remuneration is calculated.", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_33", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.8885194063186646, "score": 0.025645241141319275, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "2.34", "subsection_index": 33, "total_subsections": 37, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "2.35, 2. Litigants in person (p. 23), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "2.35 The following is a summary of the requirements for the assistance of a McKenzie Friend:", "filepath": "2. Litigants in person (p. 23)", "groups": [], "id": "2_litigants_in_person_subsection_34", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "2_litigants_in_person", "reranker_score": 1.88851