Supply of documents from court records - general", "filepath": "Court Documents", "groups": [], "id": "Part_5___Court_Documents_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Part_5___Court_Documents", "reranker_score": 1.7398196458816528, "score": 0.023624954745173454, "sourcefile": "Part 5", "sourcepage": "Court Documents", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part05", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part05", "subsection_id": "5.4", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 10, "updated": "2023-07-06T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part05"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.4, Court Documents, Part 5", "content": "5.4 D(1) A person wishing to obtain a copy of a document under rule 5.4 B or rule 5.4 C must pay any prescribed fee and -(a) if the court's permission is required, file an application notice in accordance with Part 23; or(b) if permission is not required, file a written request for the document.(2) An application for an order under rule 5.4 C(4) or for permission to obtain a copy of a document under rule 5.4 B or rule 5.4 C (except an application for permission under rule 5.4 C(6)) may be made without notice, but the court may direct notice to be given to any person who would be affected by its decision.(3) Rules 5.4, 5.4 B and 5.4 C do not apply in relation to any proceedings in respect of which a rule or practice direction makes different provision.

(Rules 5.4, 5.4 B and 5.4 C are disapplied by rules 76.34, 79.30, 80.30, 82.18 and 88.33; and rule 5.4 C is disapplied, and rule 5.4 B applied subject to court order, by paragraph 23 of Practice Direction 49 E.)

