ses of persons may only obtain a copy of a statement of case if it is edited in accordance with the directions of the court; or(d) make such other order as it thinks fit.(5) A person wishing to apply for an order under paragraph (4) must file an application notice in accordance with Part 23.(6) Where the court makes an order under paragraph (4), a non-party who wishes to obtain a copy of the statement of case, or to obtain an unedited copy of the statement of case, may apply on notice to the party or person identified in the statement of case who requested the order, for permission.", "---", "Supply of documents from court records - general
